Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Llwyn-on, Abenbury, Wales":"Llwyn-on, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["German: occupational name for a ferryman, Middle High German <i>verje</i>, <i>verge</i>."]}]},{"name":"Gruffudd","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Welsh: traditional spelling of   Griffith  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Griffith","meanings":["Welsh (Carmarthenshire and western England): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Gruffudd</i>, Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, composed of the elements <i>grip</i>, of uncertain significance, + <i>iud</i> ‘chief, lord’."]}]},{"name":"Margred","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Margaret</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margred Ferch Gruffudd was born about 1227, in Llwyn-on, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom. She had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Llewlyn ap Ynyr. She died in 1279, at the age of 53."},"et":{"abt 1227 –1279":"umbes 1227–1279","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1270–1323":"1270–1323","1270–1320":"1270–1320","1270–1344":"1270–1344","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1227–1279":"1227–1279","abt 1270 ":"umbes 1270","about 1270 ":"umbes 1270","1227":"1227","abt 1227 ":"umbes 1227","1279":"1279","1323":"1323","1344":"1344","1320":"1320","1230":"1230","1270":"1270","Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Llwyn-on, Abenbury, Wales":"Llwyn-on, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1227 –1279":"noin 1227–1279","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1270–1323":"1270–1323","1270–1320":"1270–1320","1270–1344":"1270–1344","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1227–1279":"1227–1279","abt 1270 ":"noin 1270","about 1270 ":"noin 1270","1227":"1227","abt 1227 ":"noin 1227","1279":"1279","1323":"1323","1344":"1344","1320":"1320","1230":"1230","1270":"1270","Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Llwyn-on, Abenbury, Wales":"Llwyn-on, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1227 –1279":"environ 1227–1279","1230–Male":"1230–Décédé","1270–1323":"1270–1323","1270–1320":"1270–1320","1270–1344":"1270–1344","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1227–1279":"1227–1279","abt 1270 ":"environ 1270","about 1270 ":"environ 1270","1227":"1227","abt 1227 ":"environ 1227","1279":"1279